## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the scope of the sources reviewed. Some sources may not reflect the most current strategies or legislative changes in human trafficking prevention. Additionally, the report focuses primarily on strategies applicable in the United States, which may not be directly transferable to other regions with different socio-political contexts. Further research is recommended to explore region-specific strategies and the effectiveness of implemented measures.